sentences: Gerald Cleaver (born May 4, 1963) is a jazz drummer from Detroit, Michigan.
Cleaver's father is drummer John Cleaver Jr., originally from Springfield, Ohio, and his mother was from Greenwood, Mississippi.
Cleaver joined the jazz faculty at the University of Michigan in 1995.
Under the name Veil of Names, Cleaver released an album called Adjust on the  Fresh Sound New Talent label in 2001.
